Package: NearRepeatLite
Title: Memory-Efficient Knox Test for Near-Repeat Spatio-Temporal Clustering
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Annica", "Allvin", role = c("aut", "cre"),
                  comment = c(ORCID = ""))
Description: A memory-efficient implementation of the Knox test for near-repeat
    spatio-temporal clustering. Provides NearRepeatLite(), a drop-in replacement
    for NearRepeat() from Steenbeck's NearRepeat package, for use when large
    datasets (~50,000+ events) cause memory allocation errors. Uses row-by-row
    distance computation instead of a full pairwise distance matrix, reducing
    peak RAM from O(n^2) to O(n + within-range pairs). For a dataset of 79,294
    events, peak usage drops from approximately 50 GB to under 1 GB. Output is
    fully compatible with the knox class and plot.knox() from the NearRepeat
    package. Developed for a near-repeat analysis of crime in Oslo, Norway.
License: GPL-3
Encoding: UTF-8
